    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d214fn1">Sent to Washington by the American Embassy, London,
                        apparently via military channels, and forwarded by the White House Map Room
                        by pouch on November 15, 1943; received by <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> November 20 at Oran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-12">12 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 503. Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName> personal and most secret.</p>
                <list>
                    <item>Para 1. Reference your No. 417 of 11th November.<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d214fn2">Message sent from Washington, November 10, 1943; <hi
                                rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_172">p. 172</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <item>Para 2. I have immediately telegraphed to General <persName
                            corresp="#p_ASC1">Auchinleck</persName> to render every possible
                        assistance in the constriction [<hi rend="italic">construction</hi>] of the
                        four air bases.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
